"Inoue R., Ueda S., Wakuta K., Sasaki K., Ariyama T.","Thermodynamic consideration on the absorption properties of carbon dioxide to basic oxide",2010,"ISIJ International","50","11",,"1532","1538",,,10.2355/isijinternational.50.1532,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79551593468&partnerID=40&md5=ddb17534f23365f1eb1d3acfb57958aa","Institute of Multidisciplinary Research for Advanced Materials, Tohoku University, 2-1-1 Katahira, Aoba-ku, Sendai 980-8577, Japan; Institute of Multidisciplinary Research for Advanced Materials, Tohoku University, Japan; Aichi Steel Corporation, Japan","Inoue, R., Institute of Multidisciplinary Research for Advanced Materials, Tohoku University, 2-1-1 Katahira, Aoba-ku, Sendai 980-8577, Japan; Ueda, S., Institute of Multidisciplinary Research for Advanced Materials, Tohoku University, 2-1-1 Katahira, Aoba-ku, Sendai 980-8577, Japan; Wakuta, K., Institute of Multidisciplinary Research for Advanced Materials, Tohoku University, Japan, Aichi Steel Corporation, Japan; Sasaki, K., Institute of Multidisciplinary Research for Advanced Materials, Tohoku University, 2-1-1 Katahira, Aoba-ku, Sendai 980-8577, Japan; Ariyama, T., Institute of Multidisciplinary Research for Advanced Materials, Tohoku University, 2-1-1 Katahira, Aoba-ku, Sendai 980-8577, Japan","Carbon capture and storage (CCS) is a key technology for greatly reducing CO2 emissions in the long term, and therefore a low-energy CCS process needs to be developed. This study focused on the solid absorption process using basic oxide, and thermodynamically examined the carbonation abilities of various basic oxides and compounds containing CaO, BaO or Li 2O. The CO2 absorption and desorption behavior of these materials containing alkali earth metal oxides was investigated by measuring the weight change over a wide range of temperatures from room temperature to 1 100°C in CO2 atmosphere. It was experimentally confirmed that the partial pressure of CO2 equilibrated with both Ba 2TiO4 and BaCO3 was higher than that equilibrated with both BaO and BaCO3. The formation of compound increased the equilibrium partial pressure of CO2 and lowered the starting temperature of CO2 desorption. © 2010 ISIJ.","Bao; Basic oxide; Cao; Co 2 desorption; Co2 adsorption; Co2 emissions; Global warming; Li2o","Bao; Basic oxide; Cao; Co <sub>2</sub> desorption; Co<sub>2</sub> adsorption; Co<sub>2</sub> emissions; Li<sub>2</sub>o; Absorption; Adsorption; Barium; Barium compounds; Carbon dioxide; Desorption; Global warming; Temperature",,,,,,"Metz, B., Davidson, O., Coninck, H., Loos, M., Meyer, L., (2005) IPCC Special Report of Carbon Dioxide Capture and Storage, p. 45. , Cambridge University Press, New York; (2008) Report of Development of Technology on Programmatic Capture and Effective Utilization of Carbon Dioxide, , Research Institute of Innovative Technology for the Earth (RITE),Tokyo; Chakma, A., (1997) Energy Corners. Manag, 38, pp. S51; Arashi, N., Oda, N., Yamada, M., Ota, H., Umeda, S., Tajioka, M., (1997) Energy Corners. Manag., 38, pp. S63; Iijima, M., (1999) Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Tech. Rev., 36, p. 41; Mimura, T., Yagi, Y., Takashina, T., Yoshiyama, R., Honda, A., (2005) Kagaku Kogaku Ronbunshu, 31, p. 237; Due, N.H., Chauvy, F., Herri, J.M., (2007) Energy Convers. Manag., 48, p. 1313; Bara, J., Gabriel, C.J., Lessmann, S., Carlisle, T.K., Finotello, A., Gin, D.L., Noble, R.D., (2007) Ind. Eng. Chem. Res., 46, p. 5380; Tomizaki, K., Shimizu, S., Onoda, M., Fujioka, Y., (2008) Chem. Lett., 37, p. 516; Sarkar, S.C., Bose, A., (1997) Energy Convers. Manag., 38, pp. S105; Horiuchi, R., Yasutake, A., Takatuki, S., Asanaga, N., (1998) Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Tech. Rev., 35, p. 406; Culp, J.T., Smith, M.R., Bittner, E., Bockrath, B., (2008) J. Am. Chem. Soc., 130, p. 12427; Duan, S., Chowdhury, A.F., Kai, T., Kazama, S., Fujioka, Y., (2008) Desalination, 234, p. 278; Kai, T., Kouketsu, T., Duan, S., Kazama, S., Yamada, K., (2008) Sep. Purif. Techn